\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 This is a critical year\'a0for Labour to set out the case for\'a0change:\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 for a fairer, greener and\'a0more dynamic Britain, where aspiration\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 is rewarded, where working people succeed and where\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 communities control their own destiny.\cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There can be no doubt that Britain faces serious challenges, nor that 13 years of\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Conservative government have left our country, our economy and our public services\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 on their knees and vulnerable to those challenges. But there should also be no doubt that\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 we can rise to them.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 We believe in our country and our people. What they lack is a government that shares\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 their ambition.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 We need to show people that Labour would be that government. Show not just\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 what the Tories have done to Britain but the Britain that Labour can build. A country\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 run in the interests of working people, and where politics is once again a force for good.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 This requires a bold and credible policy agenda \'96 and the National Policy Forum plays a\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 critical role in getting us there.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 These will be the \uc0\u64257 nal NPF consultations before Labour \u64257 nalises our manifesto for the next\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 election, and they are a vital opportunity for us to hear from voices across the labour\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 movement and country on some of the most pressing policy issues facing an incoming\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Labour government.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 They look at the ways Britain can prosper by ensuring growth in every part of our country,\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 by forging new, ethical trading relationships and by improving our everyday economy.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 They consider how better public services, focused on prevention and early intervention,\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 can make us happier, healthier and safer. They look at how we can support families in all\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 their wonderful diversity, and how by pushing power out of Westminster we can make our\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 neighbourhoods and communities more cohesive and prosperous.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Please do contribute your thoughts and ideas. The strength of our movement is its\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 diversity, and that is nowhere more apparent than in our democratic policymaking\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 process. It is important that we are able to draw on the thoughts and experiences of\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 our members, a\uc0\u64259 liates, stakeholders and supporters.\cf0 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Together we can give Britain\'a0the fairer, greener future it\'a0deserves.\cf0 \cb1 \
